# Mix and Remix Component Rule

Use this for every new or updated UI component in `lib/src/components/`.

## Required Architecture

- Build component styling with Mix and Remix primitives.
- Split each component into exactly two files:
  - `<component_name>_style.dart`
  - `<component_name>.dart`
- Keep style definitions in the style file and widget composition in the widget file.

## Naming Convention

- Prefer positive names and flags.
- Use `enabled` instead of `disabled`.
- Use `isVisible` instead of `isHidden`.
- Use `canInteract` instead of `cannotInteract`.

## Example

```dart
// hero_button_style.dart
class HeroButtonStyle {
  final bool enabled;
}
```

```dart
// hero_button.dart
class HeroButton extends StatelessWidget {
  const HeroButton({required this.enabled, super.key});
  final bool enabled;
}
```
